        text: "\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "'   for it in your argv() array.  If it finds it, it returns True (guess"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "'   what it returns if it DOESN'T find it.... FALSE!  Bet you didn't expect"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "'   that :p).  What's more, it also returns the array index of that switch"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "'   (for extra processing) in Position."
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "'   If that wasn't enough, it also supports pattern matching, so you can"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "'   search for special switches like \"/i:*\"."
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
